Method Detail

destroy

public void destroy()
Destroys the object correctly.

Description:
This method destroys the instance of FedmIscFunctionUnit in the native library.
It is mandatory to call this method to clean the allocated memory in the native library, but
if the method deleteChild is used, then destroy is called internally for all listed childs.
The function unit object that act as a root must always be cleared with destroy.
TIP: use destroy only for the root function unit. This destroys the complete tree structure.

sendProtocol

public int sendProtocol(byte cmdByte)
                 throws FePortDriverException,
                        FeReaderDriverException,
                        FedmException
The central communication function.

Parameters:
cmdByte - control byte
Returns:
an integer with the status byte (>=0) or error code (<0)

Description:
Protocol traffic is executed with the method sendProtocol. This gets only the control byte of the desired protocol. All the data necessary for the protocol transfer are taken from the data container. You must therefore ensure that all the protocol data have first been updated.
If an error occurs, the lastError attribute is set.

Throws:
FedmException
FeReaderDriverException
FePortDriverException

addChild

public int addChild(int outNr,
                    FedmIscFunctionUnit child)
             throws FedmException
Adds a function unit to the child list.

Parameters:
outNr - the output number where the function unit is physically connected
child - the child object which represents the physical function unit
Returns:
error code (negative value) or OK (0)

Description:
This method adds a function unit to the child list.
With this method, one can build a tree structure, which represents the physical connections
of function units. Only multiplexers can have 1..8 childs. Dynamic antenna tuners represents an
endpoint of a tree and can't have childs.
This method can throw a FedmException, if an error occurs inside the Java Native Interface.

Throws:
FedmException

deleteChild

public int deleteChild(int outNr)
                throws FedmException

Parameters:
outNr - the output number where the function unit is physically connected
Returns:
error code (negative value) or OK (0)

Description:
This method deletes a function unit from the child list.
The function unit object to be removed from the list is still existing.
This method can throw a FedmException, if an error occurs inside the Java Native Interface.

Throws:
FedmException
